4.0 of 5 bubbles
Do not book Halong Bay cruises in advance
Aug 2015 • Family
There is no need to book in advance or online. You will pay way over the odds like we did compared to when you are in Hanoi. Almost 60% more. There are literally hundreds of cruises and boats! Lots of tour agents especially if you are in the old quarter. Just book the day before.
Three nights in Hanoi is enough for me and you can have the shuttle from Halong Bay send you to the train station if you are going to SAPA by overnight train and save one night's hotel stay.
Written September 23, 2015
JaysonLO
Hong Kong, China68 contributions
7
2.0 of 5 bubbles
Be careful with the overnight boat trip
Aug 2012 • Solo
I joined a 2D1N boat trip to Halong Bay in Hanoi during weekend. Everything seemed to be fantastic until I discovered my money was stolen on the boat afterwards.
I joined the trip through booking from the hotel. I got up early and followed the guide to Halong Bay. The guide was very nice and helpful. He gave us a lot of information about Hanoi and Halong Bay. I appreciated his effort and his professionalism. It took about three hours from Hanoi to Halong Bay. We arrived there at about noon time but waited till 1.30pm before we could get on the boat.
On the boat, we were assigned our room. I had my own room because I was a single traveller. We had good lunch and then we went to see the caves and play kayak. I would say the meals provided were very good, especially I don't eat meat and poultry and requested seafood meal. They could all arranged that for me. I really appreciated that.
I had never thought that my money was stolen on boat so I left my money in my bag which was put into a drawer in my room. My room was absolutely locked before I went out. I didn't think I should bring money to visit the caves and play kayak. The thief was clever because he didn't take all my money but just some of it. If he had taken all or most of my money, I would have discovered that easily on the boat.
When I finished my trip and returned to hotel, I checked my money and found that two VND500,000 notes and two USD20 notes were missing. I was sure the money was stolen because I had not used any USD and it was put in my wallet separately from the VND. I have a habbit to count the money before and after, and every day I record how much and what I have spent. It was very bad experience but maybe good teaching. I should not have trusted people there. It was so bad that my travel was ruined by that. If that had not happened it would have been quite a perfect trip.
Since the boat trip was arranged by the hotel, I talked to the hotel manager about that incident. Though the manager called to ask the cruise company and crew members on the boat, certainly nobody would admit he was the thief. I wanted to report that to the police because it might help if I needed to claim insurance. However, the hotel manager told me that it was useless because the police would charge you first.
I write this review because I want to remind all travellers that they must be very careful. Even you put your valuables and money in a locked room, they may have gone missing. I am not sure whether I should write the name of the cruise company here because I don't know if I may violate any rules in this website (TripAdvisor), but if you want to know that, you may contact me directly.
Written August 30, 2012
Yerany H
